<page>
   <topic>DEC_TO_HEX Function</topic>
     <description>Public user defined function.</description>
     
   <syntax>Hex_Value as C = dec_to_hex(N decimal_value [,L pad ])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>decimal_value</name>
         <description>An integer value. Numeric</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>pad</name>
         <description>Logical</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
 
   <discussion>
The DEC_TO_HEX() function returns the hexadecimal equivalent of a decimal number.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
dim dnum as N
dim hnum as C
dnum = 12
hnum = dec_to_hex(dnum)
? hnum ? "C"
]]></example>
   
